cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL 

The paper deals with cross-modal hashing, which involves mapping multimedia data into a common Hamming space for retrieval purposes. This falls under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on visual and textual modalities, cs.CV and cs.MM are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IR for retrieval purposes, and cs.LG and cs.CL for the machine learning and natural language processing aspects.
